cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.SI 

This paper is primarily focused on detecting malware variants in Android devices using behavior-based analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper also discusses the design and implementation of a framework for malware detection, which falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also proposes the use of interception techniques and signature generation, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments conducted in the paper involve collecting and analyzing a large dataset, which can be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of the proposed system on device performance and battery life, which can be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
